article.headline: Nicholls State 100, MD Eastern Shore 66
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. (AP) -- Jason Wilkins scored 26 points and made eight 3-pointers as Nicholls State beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 100-66 on Saturday night. Nicholls led 55-29 at halftime and never gave up the lead in the game. Besides Wilkins, Nicholls (3-5) had three other players in double digits. Adonis Gray had 16 points, Searles 14 and Depron 10. Maryland-Eastern Shore (1-6) was led by Jareem Dowling with 18 points. Corey Brown added 12 and Jason McKinnon 10. Nicholls outrebounded Maryland-Eastern Shore 39-33 and had 20 assists to Maryland-Eastern Shore's 12. Nicholls shot 53 percent from the floor for the game while Maryland-Eastern Shore shot 42 percent.
